### 📊 Centralized Metrics & Business Operations (FactInventory Table)

To establish the analytical core of the Star Schema, a centralized Fact table (`dbo.FactInventory`) was engineered to capture transactional inventory baselines. This table acts as the foundational ledger, storing foreign keys (`DateKey`, `ProductKey`, `FactoryKey`) that map directly to the surrounding dimension tables. It stores quantitative, additive business metrics—such as physical volumes (`OnHandQty`, `AvailableQty`, `ReservedQty`, `InTransitQty`) and financial exposures (`InventoryValue`)—forming the basis for all downstream analytical visualizations and KPI data aggregations.

#### T-SQL Fact Inventory DDL & Data Population Script:

-- 1) Run this
/*CREATE TABLE dbo.FactInventory
    (
        FactInventoryKey INT IDENTITY(1,1) PRIMARY KEY,
        DateKey INT NOT NULL,
        ProductKey INT NOT NULL,
        FactoryKey INT NOT NULL,
        OnHandQty DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
        AvailableQty DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
        ReservedQty DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
        InTransitQty DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL,
        InventoryValue DECIMAL(18,2) NOT NULL
    );*/


	-- 2)
DECLARE @InvBatch TABLE (DateKey INT, 
SKU VARCHAR(60), 
FactoryCode VARCHAR(30),
OnHandQty DECIMAL(18,2), 
AvailableQty DECIMAL(18,2), 
ReservedQty DECIMAL(18,2), 
InTransitQty DECIMAL(18,2), 
InventoryValue DECIMAL(18,2));




SELECT ib.DateKey, p.ProductKey, f.FactoryKey, ib.OnHandQty, ib.AvailableQty, ib.ReservedQty, ib.InTransitQty, ib.InventoryValue
FROM @InvBatch ib
JOIN dbo.DimProduct p ON p.SKU = ib.SKU
JOIN dbo.DimFactory f ON f.FactoryCode = ib.FactoryCode;





--3)
select * from dbo.FactInventory







